menu "Cadenza candidate hardware"

config CADENZA_T_EMBED_RUNTIME
    bool "Build the complete T-Embed display/input/App runtime"
    default n
    help
        Link the portable runtime and bundled Apps with the ESP-IDF esp_lcd
        ST7789 and GPIO encoder adapters. The hardware candidate enables this
        together with speaker, microphone and USB Audio.

config CADENZA_T_EMBED_MICROPHONE
    bool "Use the physical T-Embed ES7210 microphone instead of synthetic PCM"
    default n
    help
        Build and execute the researched ES7210/I2S1 adapter. Leave disabled
        when no physical original T-Embed is connected. The adapter source is
        compiled in either mode so CI still checks the SDK integration.

config CADENZA_T_EMBED_SPEAKER
    bool "Use the physical T-Embed MAX98357A speaker output"
    default n
    help
        Build and execute the ESP-IDF 5 I2S0 output adapter. It owns a task,
        DMA channel and buffers independent from the I2S1 microphone adapter.

config CADENZA_CONNECTIVITY_RUNTIME
    bool "Build ESP-IDF Wi-Fi, NimBLE and Security 2 adapter"
    depends on CADENZA_T_EMBED_RUNTIME
    default y
    help
        Connect the portable capability/lease-driven connectivity service to
        ESP-IDF Wi-Fi/IP events, NimBLE GAP roles and the official BLE Wi-Fi
        provisioning manager. Security 0 is not supported by this adapter;
        Security 2 material must come from the privileged platform hook.

endmenu
